<div class="entry-content"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-snippet-basic-buttons"><a href="#recipe" data-recipe="3276" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #000000;border-color: #333333;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-jump-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" fill="#ffffff"><path data-color="color-2" d="M9,2h6c0.6,0,1-0.4,1-1s-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,0,8,0.4,8,1S8.4,2,9,2z"></path> <path fill="#ffffff" d="M16,11V5c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,4,8,4.4,8,5v6H1.9L12,23.6L22.1,11H16z"></path></g></svg></span> Jump to Recipe</a>

<a href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wprm_print/3276" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #000000;border-color: #333333;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-print-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent" data-recipe-id="3276" data-template="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#ffffff" d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.569,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18.552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print Recipe</a></div><input class="jpibfi" type="hidden"><p><em>These Homemade Corn Tortillas are still the most popular recipe on the site, so if you're new to them please consider giving it a go!&nbsp; I've updated this post with tips for the most common obstacles you'll encounter when making tortillas for the first time&nbsp; -- plus some brand options if you're new to Masa Harina.&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></p>
<p>Imagine walking into the grocery store early one morning and seeing this:</p>
<div id="attachment_1635" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-1635"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1635" class="wp-image-1635 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20455'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Homemade Corn Tortillas are so easy! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="455" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico-600x427.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico-300x213.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico-500x355.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1635" class="wp-image-1635 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico.jpg" alt="Homemade Corn Tortillas are so easy! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="455" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico-600x427.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico-300x213.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tortilla-dough-for-corn-tortillas-chedraui-cozumel-mexico-500x355.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></a><p id="caption-attachment-1635" class="wp-caption-text">Cozumel, Mexico -- Photo by Chloe Miller</p></div>
<p>That's the dough used to make fresh corn tortillas each morning in the markets of Cozumel.</p>
<p>Producers will de-hydrate this corn dough and sell it in bags like this:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1634 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20511'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Big bag of Maseca Masa Harina for homemade corn tortillas" width="640" height="511" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour-600x479.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour-300x240.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour-500x399.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1634 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour.jpg" alt="Big bag of Maseca Masa Harina for homemade corn tortillas" width="640" height="511" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour-600x479.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour-300x240.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-flour-500x399.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>This is Masa Harina and it's your golden ticket to easy homemade corn tortillas!</p>
<p>Add some water, a bit of salt, and you've got masa on your hands -- which means you're only a few minutes away from an authentic stack of tortillas.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span style="color: #0000ff;"><a style="color: #0000ff;" href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/what-is-masa-harina/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">What exactly is Masa Harina?</a></span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-10647 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20816%20680'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Making your own corn tortillas at home will give you a massive upgrade in flavor compared to store-bought tortillas. They are cheaper too! " width="816" height="680" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg 816w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-300x250.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-768x640.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 816px) 100vw, 816px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-10647 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" alt="Making your own corn tortillas at home will give you a massive upgrade in flavor compared to store-bought tortillas. They are cheaper too! " width="816" height="680" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg 816w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-300x250.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-768x640.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 816px) 100vw, 816px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Making a batch of these&nbsp;beauties&nbsp;comes with two main benefits, the most obvious being a stack of&nbsp;corn tortillas that are good enough to be eaten on their own.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8177" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20825%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Take a bite out of a corn tortilla." width="825" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg 825w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-300x233.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-768x596.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-500x388.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-600x465.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8177" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" alt="Take a bite out of a corn tortilla." width="825" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg 825w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-300x233.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-768x596.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-500x388.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-600x465.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px" /></noscript></p>
<p>The other, hidden benefit is&nbsp;that your taste buds will now have a built-in tortillameter that you can use to gauge the quality of tortillas sold in your neighborhood.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
<p>This&nbsp;will help you stay away from store-bought tortillas that have strayed too far from the original process.</p>
<h2>How To Make Corn Tortillas</h2>
<p>First things first, get some Masa Harina in the house!</p>
<p>Here are the three brands that are most common in the States:&nbsp; Bob's Red Mill, Maseca, and Gold Mine.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8163" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20887%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Here are 3 different Masa Harinas to choose from for your next batch of tamales or corn tortillas. Yum!! mexicanplease.com" width="887" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From.jpg 887w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-300x216.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-768x554.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-500x361.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-600x433.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 887px) 100vw, 887px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8163" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From.jpg" alt="Here are 3 different Masa Harinas to choose from for your next batch of tamales or corn tortillas. Yum!! mexicanplease.com" width="887" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From.jpg 887w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-300x216.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-768x554.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-500x361.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-600x433.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 887px) 100vw, 887px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Maseca is the most common brand and it's a worthy starting point.&nbsp; Lately I prefer the flavor of Bob's Red Mill so keep an eye out for that one too.&nbsp; <a href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/3-different-masa-harinas-choose/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">More info on comparing these Masa Harina brands.</a></p>
<p><strong>Update:&nbsp;</strong> Bob's Red Mill also sells an organic Masa Harina.&nbsp; <a href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/organic-masa-harina-options/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">More details on organic Masa Harina options.&nbsp;</a></p>
<p>Okay, here's your starting recipe:</p>
<p>2 cups Masa Harina<br />
1.5 cups of warm water<br />
1/2 teaspoon salt</p>
<p>Add the&nbsp;2 cups of Masa Harina&nbsp;and 1/2 teaspoon&nbsp;salt to a mixing bowl.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9820" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20779%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="1 cup masa harina" width="779" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3.jpg 779w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3-300x246.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3-768x631.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3-500x411.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 779px) 100vw, 779px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9820" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3.jpg" alt="1 cup masa harina" width="779" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3.jpg 779w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3-300x246.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3-768x631.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-3-500x411.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 779px) 100vw, 779px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Add one cup of the warm water and stir until all of the water is absorbed.&nbsp;</p>
<p>It will probably look like this:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1633 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20427'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Homemade Corn Tortillas so easy! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water-500x334.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1633 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water.jpg" alt="Homemade Corn Tortillas so easy! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-adding-water-500x334.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Now start adding the rest of the warm water incrementally, a couple tablespoons at a time, and stirring regularly.</p>
<p>The idea is to keep adding water until the flour bits meld into a dough.&nbsp; At that point you can pick it up with your hands and knead it together.</p>
<p>Eventually it will look like this:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1632 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20427'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump-500x334.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1632 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump.jpg" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-maseca-after-rolling-into-clump-500x334.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Next, separate the dough into golf ball sized chunks, rolling them between your hands to form a smooth ball.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This will make the tortillas about 4 inches across.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1627 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20427'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls-500x334.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1627 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls.jpg" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-balls-500x334.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>You'll need something to put on either side of the dough ball to prevent it from sticking when you flatten it.&nbsp;</p>
<p>You can use plastic wrap, but I’ve found that a large Ziploc bag cut in half works best:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1630 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20427'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Putting a masa dough ball in a tortilla press" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press-500x334.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1630 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press.jpg" alt="Putting a masa dough ball in a tortilla press" width="640" height="427" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-doughball-in-tortilla-press-500x334.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>So that’s half a Ziploc bag on either side of the dough ball.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>And after flattening it the plastic should peel off effortlessly.&nbsp; If it’s sticking then there's probably too much water in the dough.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1628 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20480'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="After flattening a masa dough ball in the tortilla press" width="640" height="480" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening-600x450.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening-300x225.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening-500x375.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1628 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening.jpg" alt="After flattening a masa dough ball in the tortilla press" width="640" height="480" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening-600x450.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening-300x225.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-dough-after-flattening-500x375.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<h2>Do I Really Need A Tortilla Press?</h2>
<p>No, you definitely don't need a tortilla press, so please don't let that stop you from making your own tortillas!</p>
<p>You can use a skillet or any flat-bottomed dish to squish 'em.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Here I'm using a casserole dish and it's just as effective as a tortilla press.&nbsp; Just be sure to put plastic on either side of the dough ball before flattening it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1624 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20449'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="449" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas-600x421.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas-300x210.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas-500x351.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1624 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas.jpg" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="449" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas-600x421.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas-300x210.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/flattening-dough-ball-homemade-corn-tortillas-500x351.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<h2>How To Cook Your Corn Tortillas</h2>
<p>Okay, there are two schools of thought when it comes to cooking the tortillas.</p>
<p>The first simply cooks them on each side for about a minute, or until brown spots start to appear on the underside.</p>
<p>The second school flips the tortilla 10 seconds after putting it on the skillet and then cooks each side for about a minute.&nbsp; The idea is that those first 10 seconds will seal in some of the heat and help the insides cook quicker.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8167" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20739%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Corn tortilla puffing up in a small skillet." width="739" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11.jpg 739w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11-300x260.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11-500x433.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11-600x520.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 739px) 100vw, 739px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8167" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11.jpg" alt="Corn tortilla puffing up in a small skillet." width="739" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11.jpg 739w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11-300x260.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11-500x433.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-11-600x520.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 739px) 100vw, 739px" /></noscript></p>
<p>I’ve found the second method makes the tortillas lighter and fluffier, so I use that one.&nbsp; It’s a little bit more work, but I think it’s worth it.</p>
<p>So again...heat the skillet to medium-high heat.&nbsp; Add a tortilla and flip after 10 seconds, then cook each side for about a minute or until brown spots form on each side.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1623 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20392'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="392" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three-600x368.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three-300x184.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three-500x306.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1623 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three.jpg" alt="Ahh tortillas, the cradle of Mexican cuisine. It's surprisingly easy to make a batch of fresh, homemade corn tortillas that might just convert you over for life. So good! mexicanplease.com" width="640" height="392" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three.jpg 640w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three-600x368.jpg 600w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three-300x184.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-corn-tortillas-cooking-on-comal-three-500x306.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p class="normal">Don’t be surprised if they start to puff up during cooking, that’s a good sign!</p>
<p>You can also try pressing down on them with a spatula once you flip to the final side -- sometimes this will make them puff up instantly!</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10648" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20863%20680'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Use a spatula to make your corn tortillas puff up" width="863" height="680" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal.jpg 863w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal-300x236.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal-768x605.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 863px) 100vw, 863px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10648" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal.jpg" alt="Use a spatula to make your corn tortillas puff up" width="863" height="680" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal.jpg 863w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal-300x236.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Two-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-comal-768x605.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 863px) 100vw, 863px" /></noscript></p>
<p class="normal">Eventually, you’ll have a stack of warm, steaming corn tortillas.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10647" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20816%20680'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="14 corn tortillas after cooking on comal" width="816" height="680" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg 816w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-300x250.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-768x640.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 816px) 100vw, 816px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10647" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" alt="14 corn tortillas after cooking on comal" width="816" height="680" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel.jpg 816w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-300x250.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stack-of-homemade-corn-tortillas-on-towel-768x640.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 816px) 100vw, 816px" /></noscript></p>
<p>They are best eaten as soon as possible.&nbsp; If you want some friends for life feel free to share with neighbors.</p>
<h2>Tips For Making Tortillas The First Time</h2>
<p>There are two main sources of frustration that you should know about before venturing into tortilla land.&nbsp;</p>
<p>First, getting the consistency of the dough right can take some fiddling.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9818" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20778%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Forming dough ball from masa harina" width="778" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5.jpg 778w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5-300x247.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5-768x632.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5-500x411.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 778px) 100vw, 778px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9818" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5.jpg" alt="Forming dough ball from masa harina" width="778" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5.jpg 778w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5-300x247.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5-768x632.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-5-500x411.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 778px) 100vw, 778px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Ideally, you can handle the dough without it sticking to your hands.&nbsp; If it's sticky then simply add a few sprinklings of Masa Harina to dry it out.&nbsp;</p>
<p>And conversely, if the dough is crumbly and not coming together then it means you are low on water.&nbsp; Simply add splashes of water until it forms a cohesive ball.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8160" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20925%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Kneading masa dough into a cohesive ball." width="925" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4.jpg 925w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-300x208.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-768x531.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-500x346.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-600x415.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 925px) 100vw, 925px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8160" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4.jpg" alt="Kneading masa dough into a cohesive ball." width="925" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4.jpg 925w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-300x208.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-768x531.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-500x346.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-4-600x415.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 925px) 100vw, 925px" /></noscript></p>
<p>That's why I typically recommend adding the final 1/2 cup of water incrementally -- this will help you find the right consistency quicker.&nbsp;</p>
<p>And the second pitfall is the temp of the stove.&nbsp; You might need to make a tortilla sacrifice to get the temperature of the stove right so don't sweat it if this happens!</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-9813 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20745%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Quick flipping a corn tortilla in the skillet" width="745" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11.jpg 745w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11-300x258.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11-500x430.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-9813 size-full" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11.jpg" alt="Quick flipping a corn tortilla in the skillet" width="745" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11.jpg 745w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11-300x258.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-11-500x430.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /></noscript>&nbsp;</p>
<p>For my stove that means a little over medium heat does the job.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This will have brown spots forming on the underside in about 60 seconds or so.&nbsp; This also makes it easy to flip the tortilla with your fingers as it will be sliding around the pan in a matter of seconds when the temp is right.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
<p>If it's taking significantly longer for brown spots to form then you'll need to raise the heat.&nbsp; Conversely, if you're getting black spots forming in a matter of seconds then you need to lower the heat.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9814" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20786%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Taking a bite from homemade corn tortilla" width="786" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9.jpg 786w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9-300x244.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9-768x625.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9-500x407.jpg 500w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9814" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9.jpg" alt="Taking a bite from homemade corn tortilla" width="786" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9.jpg 786w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9-300x244.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9-768x625.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Testing-Masa-Harina-from-Masienda-9-500x407.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px" /></noscript></p>
<h2>How To Store Corn Tortillas</h2>
<p>These are best eaten right off the skillet!&nbsp; But you can keep them warm&nbsp;by simply wrapping them in a tea towel or by using a dedicated tortilla warmer.&nbsp;</p>
<p>They'll keep for a few days in the fridge, but don't forget that you'll need to reheat them to bring them back to life after they have chilled down.&nbsp;</p>
<p>I always use a dry skillet over medium heat to do this -- simply add as many tortillas as you need to the skillet and give them 30-60 seconds per side to warm up.&nbsp; Using the stovetop will also crisp them up slightly and that's when they are most tasty.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6456" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20739%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Here's the recipe for a recent batch of homemade corn tortillas I made using some White Olotillo Corn. I used a food processor to grind the corn down and added in some Masa Harina to get the right consistency. mexicanplease.com" width="739" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate.jpg 739w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate-300x260.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate-500x433.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate-600x520.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 739px) 100vw, 739px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6456" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate.jpg" alt="Here's the recipe for a recent batch of homemade corn tortillas I made using some White Olotillo Corn. I used a food processor to grind the corn down and added in some Masa Harina to get the right consistency. mexicanplease.com" width="739" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate.jpg 739w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate-300x260.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate-500x433.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/white-olotillo-corn-tortillas-stacked-on-plate-600x520.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 739px) 100vw, 739px" /></noscript></p>
<h2>Can I Freeze The Tortilla Dough?</h2>
<p>I haven't tried freezing the masa dough but I 've gotten multiple emails saying it doesn't work!&nbsp; Once thawed the masa dough seems to be crumbly.&nbsp; Sure, you could probably add some water to rebuild it, but it would probably be quicker and tastier to start over.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
<p>Instead, I will sometimes use only half of the dough to make tortillas and store the rest of it in the fridge where it will keep for at least a few days.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Simply wrap the leftover dough in plastic and foil, and then store it in the fridge.&nbsp; The next day you can pull off a chunk, flatten it, and cook up a warm, homemade tortilla in a matter of minutes 🙂</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8177" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20825%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Take a bite out of a corn tortilla." width="825" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg 825w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-300x233.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-768x596.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-500x388.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-600x465.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8177" src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" alt="Take a bite out of a corn tortilla." width="825" height="640" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-corn-tortillas/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Homemade Corn Tortillas" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg" srcset="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16.jpg 825w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-300x233.jpg 300w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-768x596.jpg 768w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-500x388.jpg 500w, https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/3-Different-Masa-Harinas-To-Choose-From-16-600x465.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Okay, I hope this solves Homemade Corn Tortillas for you!&nbsp; &nbsp;For reference, here are some additional articles on my site to fill in any gaps:</p>
