</div><div class="feast-prev-next"><div class="feast-prev-post">&laquo; <a aria-label="Previous post: " href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/easy-enchiladas-verdes/" rel="prev">Easy Enchiladas Verdes</a></div><div class="feast-next-post"><a aria-label="Next post: " href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/mango-black-bean-salsa/" rel="next">Mango Black Bean Salsa</a> &raquo;</div></div><footer class="entry-footer"></footer></article><h2 class="screen-reader-text">Reader Interactions</h2><div class="entry-comments" id="comments"><h3>Comments</h3><ol class="comment-list">
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-93839">
	<article id="article-comment-93839">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Missing Mexican Food</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">January 04, 2026 at 9:06 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.mexicanplease.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
I grew up eating corn tortillas. Now that I have moved to India, the masa here isn’t great. The tortillas either blacken or stay bright yellow. They don’t puff up. I’m so frustrated. Also they are a little gummy. I cook them for a minute on each side, but it isn’t long enough even with the heat nearly on high. It never browns. 😔 I want proper corn tortillas without importing masa. I can’t buy my own mill, either. Any ideas?</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-93839' data-commentid="93839" data-postid="1622" data-belowelement="article-comment-93839" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Missing Mexican Food" aria-label='Reply to Missing Mexican Food'>Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-patrick bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-94375">
	<article id="article-comment-94375">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Patrick</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">January 23, 2026 at 5:00 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Ooh tough one MMF.  To me it sounds like that masa harina might not be the real thing, maybe more akin to cornmeal.  I've made my own masa at home using a food processor, have you seen that post?  I will link it below.  I hope these help:</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/masa-harina-vs-cornmeal/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc">Masa Harina vs. Cornmeal:  What's the Difference?</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.mexicanplease.com/homemade-masa-dough-using-yellow-field-corn/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc">Making Masa with a Food Processor</a></p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-94375' data-commentid="94375" data-postid="1622" data-belowelement="article-comment-94375" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Patrick" aria-label='Reply to Patrick'>Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
